9969925,-0.00311867,-0.00368667,0.03521848,-0.05710651,0.04637871,0.03328041,-0.02186313,0.01468147,0.00444475,0.05022052,-0.02862072,0.08363261,0.00536386,-0.05681475,-0.01031470,0.00095523,-0.04677139,-0.07370348,0.02848972,-0.05550099,0.01400712,0.02661148,-0.05134269,-0.04809257,-0.02272966,0.00910167,0.00874480,0.01227168,0.00346612,-0.00040819,0.02291128,0.03575149,0.01583926,0.02698582,0.01735185,-0.05146533,0.05818976,0.02438867,0.03483876,0.09666581,0.01805938,0.06971041]',E'Creating new pipelines\n\nPhoenix allows us to create our own custom pipelines anywhere in the router. To do so, we call the [`pipeline/2`](`Phoenix.Router.pipeline/2`) macro with these arguments: an atom for the name of our new pipeline and a block with all the plugs we want in it.\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule HelloWeb.Router do\n  use HelloWeb, :router','{"source": "phoenix", "version": "1.7", "language": "elixir", "title": "Routing", "section_title": "routing", "url": "https://github.com/phoenixframework/phoenix/blob/main/guides/routing.md", "topics": "phoenix,elixir,routing", "categories": "web,elixir,fullstack,realtime"}');
