964717,0.03964100,0.00513529,0.00355851,-0.01822066,-0.02019439,0.07808750,0.04529013,-0.01610373,-0.07016204,0.10416353,0.01813163,0.06526160,-0.01188729,-0.00071228,-0.01064029,0.00623499,-0.00910460,-0.00312922,0.06869116,-0.01080243,-0.02922197,-0.02699824,-0.01092448,-0.04851578,0.04648304,-0.02315486,-0.01702511,-0.00176544,0.02743609,-0.03273205,-0.02310938,0.04032340,0.01735310,-0.01820141,-0.02139717,-0.02778007,0.04885640,0.00659842,-0.00015550,0.10986290,-0.01333529,0.04977089]',E'Rendering\n\n[`render/3`] will also pass the value which the `show` action received for `messenger` from the parameters as an assign.\n\nIf we need to pass values into the template when using `render`, that''s easy. We can pass a keyword like we''ve seen with `messenger: messenger`, or we can use `Plug.Conn.assign/3`, which conveniently returns `conn`.\n\n```elixir\n  def show(conn, %{"messenger" => messenger}) do\n    conn\n    |> Plug.Conn.assign(:messenger, messenger)\n    |> render(:show)\n  end\n```','{"source": "phoenix", "version": "1.7", "language": "elixir", "title": "Controllers", "section_title": "controllers", "url": "https://github.com/phoenixframework/phoenix/blob/main/guides/controllers.md", "topics": "phoenix,elixir,controllers", "categories": "web,elixir,fullstack,realtime"}');
