7,0.03040801,-0.01780081,0.01500280,0.03271823,0.03291579,0.10933220,-0.03308776,-0.03656307,0.04432216,0.04610404,0.04644841,0.04201028,0.00506642,-0.02962292,-0.02606237,-0.03546276,-0.00801559,-0.00424899,0.02037902,-0.00678621,0.05749341,-0.00432019,-0.05500350,-0.00852467,0.02506197,-0.00664399,-0.02267778,0.01180282,-0.01604110,-0.00552686,0.00775501,0.01090122,0.09029894,0.01963829,0.02220157,0.00536153,0.04586532,0.04894958,0.00066395,0.02207953,0.08546313,0.05411743]',E'New rendering formats\n\npipeline :browser do\n    plug :accepts, ["html", "json"]\n    plug :fetch_session\n    plug :fetch_live_flash\n    plug :put_root_layout, html: {HelloWeb.LayoutView, :root}\n    plug :protect_from_forgery\n    plug :put_secure_browser_headers\n  end\n...\n```\n\nPhoenix allows us to change formats on the fly with the `_format` query string parameter. If we go to [`http://localhost:4000/?_format=json`](http://localhost:4000/?_format=json), we will see `%{"message": "this is some JSON"}`.','{"source": "phoenix", "version": "1.7", "language": "elixir", "title": "Controllers", "section_title": "controllers", "url": "https://github.com/phoenixframework/phoenix/blob/main/guides/controllers.md", "topics": "phoenix,elixir,controllers", "categories": "web,elixir,fullstack,realtime"}');
